Generowanie ciÄ…gÃ³w Haltona, Sobolâ€™a oraz ciÄ…gÃ³w z rozkÅ‚adem jednostajnym za pomocÄ… randtoolbox

  xlab("X") + ylab("Y")

  geom_point(color='darkcyan') +
  xlab("X") + ylab("Y") 
img3 <- ggplot(df, aes(x=Random1, y=Random2)) +
  geom_point(color='darkblue') +
  xlab("X") + ylab("Y") 
img <- ggarrange(img1, img2, img3, 
          labels = c("Halton", "Sobol", "Random"),
          ncol = 2, nrow = 2)

Zmodyfikowana funkcja BlackScholesâ€™a z uÅ¼yciem ciÄ…gÃ³w o niskiej rozbieÅ¼noÅ›ci o rozkÅ‚adzie normalnym

prices <- c(196, 161, 170)
calls <- NULL
puts <- NULL
for (i in prices){
  tmp <- GBSOption(TypeFlag = "c", S = i, X = 184, Time = 3/52, r = 0.03,
                   b = 0.03, sigma = 0.20)@price
  calls <- rbind(calls, tmp)
  tmp <- GBSOption(TypeFlag = "p", S = i, X = 184, Time = 3/52, r = 0.03,
                   b = 0.03, sigma = 0.20)@price
  puts <- rbind(puts, tmp)
}
df <- data.frame(unlist(prices), unlist(calls), unlist(puts))
names(df) <- c("Cena opcji, PLN", "CALL", "PUT")
rownames(df) <- df$prices
pander(df, type = 'grid')

WedÅ‚ug estymacji optymalnÄ… kopulÄ… bÄ™dzie kopula Gaussa. SprÃ³bujmy dopasowaÄ‡ sugerowany model za pomocÄ… pakietu copula i dokÅ‚adnie sprawdziÄ‡ dopasowane parametry.

Zasymulujmy 10000 prÃ³b korzystajÄ…c z parametrÃ³w i zrÃ³bmy wykresy

x_mean <- mean(df$HPE)
x_var <- var(df$HPE)
x_rate <- x_mean / x_var
x_shape <- ( (x_mean)^2 ) / x_var

y_mean <- mean(df$DELL)
y_var <- var(df$DELL)
y_rate <- y_mean / y_var
y_shape <- ( (y_mean)^2 ) / y_var


my_dist <- mvdc(normalCopula(par_2, dim=2),
                margins = c("gamma","gamma"),
                paramMargins = list(list(shape = x_shape, 
                                         rate = x_rate), 
                              list(shape = y_shape, 
                                   rate = y_rate)
                                    )
                )
v <- rMvdc(5000, my_dist)
pdf_mvd <- dMvdc(v, my_dist) #gÄ™stoÅ›Ä‡
cdf_mvd <- pMvdc(v, my_dist) #dystrybuanta

img1 <- scatterplot3d(v[, 1], v[, 2],
                      pdf_mvd, 
                      color="blue", 
                      main="Density", 
                      xlab = "u1", 
                      ylab="u2", 
                      zlab="pMvdc",
                      pch=".")

img2 <- scatterplot3d(v[, 1],v[, 2], 
                      cdf_mvd, 
                      color="green", 
                      main="CDF", 
                      xlab = "u1", 
                      ylab="u2", 
                      zlab="pMvdc",
                      pch=".")
